Though the author is correct in advising to do exception handling like this[1] instead of this[2], they are not correct in the reasoning behind it. In method [2], if a writer cannot be instanciated, the code will still try to write with it, which will probably cause a NullPointerException. Rewriting to method [1] hinders this.<p>[1]:<p><pre><code>  Writer writer = null;
  try {
      writer = new FileWriter(&quot;/tmp/a&quot;);
      writer.write(&quot;Line1&quot;);
      writer.close();
  } catch(FileNotFoundException e) {
      // handle error
  } catch (IOException ex) {
      // handle error
  }

